clude those `add-opens` directives.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing JVM arguments for coverage**\\n\\nI see that the local scaffold includes `jvmArgs` in build.gradle, but the driver isn't set up deterministically. It doesn't need to restate that. The question about `add-opens` comes up—can it be applied before getting meaningful coverage? Since OGNL employs reflection for `setAccessible`, and the existing build indicates we need this for JDK tests, I have to consider that reflecting on private access might require `java.lang` opening.\\n\\nWith JDK17+ blocking `setAccessible`, existing tests might use `Method.setAccessible(true)` for custom class loading. I should inspect any warnings and research sources like `javassist`. The current setup works with `java.lang`, and it seems we should avoid `--illegal-access` since that was removed in JDK25.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing scaffold gaps for coverage**\\n\\nWhen generated from scratch, the normal scaffold seems to lack `jvmArgs`, which could hinder meaningful coverage for expression compilation using javassist. I really need some guidance on this. Additionally, there's the determination of dependencies: the artifact POM has a runtime dependency on `org.javassist:javassist:3.29.0-GA`, which is resolved transitively. So, it appears I don’t need any extra dependencies, but I need to ensure everything is properly set up for effective testing!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"OGNL is an in-process expression/reflection library and its only runtime dependency, Javassist, is already transitive from ognl:ognl:3.3.5; no Docker or extra Maven dependency is needed. Meaningful JVM coverage of its reflection/expression-compiler paths does need JDK module-opening test setup on modern JDKs, which is also reflected by the existing OGNL test scaffold and upstream JDK17+ test profile.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Configure generated JVM tests with Test.jvmArgs including `--add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED`. If tests exercise OGNL reflection against JDK collection internals, also add `--add-opens=java.base/java.util=ALL-UNNAMED`, matching OGNL's upstream JDK17+ test profile. Do not set `ognl.security.manager` or `ognl.UseJDK9PlusAccessHandler` globally unless a specific test needs that path; set and restore such properties inside the test.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"SecurityManager-based OGNL coverage is fragile on JDK 25 because SecurityManager APIs are terminally deprecated/being removed.\",\n    \"Javassist expression-compilation coverage may behave differently in native image than on the JVM; keep native-image expectations separate from JVM setup.\",\n    \"OGNL reads some system properties during static initialization, so property-based tests must isolate class initialization order.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09b83899c3f57380016a3f08ac02cc81959904a6ea157a663b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1210, "output": 1256, "cacheRead": 45568, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 48034, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782515868453, "responseId": "resp_09b83899c3f57380016a3f089ce6808195a06f536f9902dda1"}}
